  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "Two novellas and five short stories filling in the months around Isstvan. John French's The Crimson Fist follows Captain Alexis Polux as the Iron Warriors snare the Imperial Fists' retribution fleet in a void ambush at Phall. Aaron Dembski-Bowden's Prince of Crows watches Night Lords first captain Sevatar police his own primarch's collapsing mind on the death world Tsagualsa. Dan Abnett's The Lightning Tower puts Rogal Dorn alone in his study as he readies Terra for siege; Graham McNeill's The Dark King and Death of a Silversmith trace Konrad Curze from the slums of Nostramo to the present; Gav Thorpe's Raven's Flight rides with Corax breaking out of the Isstvan V trap; and McNeill's The Kaban Project surfaces a forbidden Mechanicum AI inside the loyalist machine cult.",
